    {
      "text": "Survival Kids, known as Stranded Kids in Europe, is a 1999 survival video game developed and published by Konami for the Game Boy Color. The gameplay revolves around surviving on a deserted island, and features an open-ended structure that presents the player with multiple ways to progress. It is the first in the Survival Kids series in Japan, which goes under the name Lost in Blue in North America and Europe. \nSurvival Kids received its first official re-release on the Nintendo Classics service on May 23, 2025.",
